  "text": "We start with a brief outline of the basics of magnetohydrodynamics, consider then both seed field generation mechanisms and dynamo amplification processes. We consider the possibility of magnetizing the universe through outflows from starbursting galaxies and AGN. We finally discuss the possible role of primordial magnetic fields created perhaps in an early universe phase transition. We focus on magnetic fields on scales larger than galaxies here, as such fields will also be the focus of SKA type telescopes, and do not discuss stellar or planetary magnetism. An extensive review of several aspects of astrophysical magnetic fields and nonlinear dynamos can be found in [CITATION_1] .",
